Text To Speech =
This learning object describes the basic mechanisms of gas exchange among the lungs, blood, and tissues.
Gas moves from areas of high pressure to areas of lower pressure.
The pressure of oxygen is represented as PO2.
PO2 in the pulmonary capillaries = 40 mm Hg.
The PCO2 in the pulmonary capillary blood equals 45 mm Hg.
The oxygenated blood moves to the tissues to deliver oxygen and "pick up" carbon dioxide that is produced from cellular metabolism.
PO2 of tissues = 40 mm Hg. PCO2 of tissues = 45 mm Hg.
